<http://status.aws.amazon.com/|Informational message: Increased API Error Rates>
We are investigating increased API error rates and latencies in a single Availability Zone in the EU-WEST-2 Region.

<http://status.aws.amazon.com/|Informational message: Increased API Error Rates>
We are investigating increased API error rates and latencies in the EU-WEST-2 Region.

<http://status.aws.amazon.com/|Informational message: Elevated API faults and alarm delays>
We are investigating increased faults for CloudWatch alarms APIs and delays in processing some alarms in the EU-WEST-2 Region.

<http://status.aws.amazon.com/|Informational message: Increased API Error Rates>
We continue to investigate the increased error rates and latencies for the EC2 APIs in the EU-WEST-2 Region. The health of existing EC2 instances is not affected.

<http://status.aws.amazon.com/|Informational message: Increased API Error Rates>
We have identified the root cause of the increase in error rates and latencies for the ELB APIs in the EU-WEST-2 Region and continue to work towards full recovery.

<http://status.aws.amazon.com/|Informational message: Elevated API faults and alarm delays>
We can confirm an elevated rate of CloudWatch Alarms API faults and delays in processing some alarms in EU-WEST-2 Region and continue to work towards full recovery.

<http://status.aws.amazon.com/|Service is operating normally: [RESOLVED] Increased API Error Rates>
Between 7:40 PM and 9:35 PM PDT we experienced increased API error rates and latencies in the EU-WEST-2 Region. The issue has been resolved and the service is operating normally.

<http://status.aws.amazon.com/|Service is operating normally: [RESOLVED] Elevated API faults and alarm delays>
Between 8:27 PM and 9:55 PM PDT, customers may have experienced elevated alarms API faults and delayed alarms in the EU-WEST-2 Region. We have resolved the issue and the service is operating normally.

<http://status.aws.amazon.com/|Informational message: Elevated error rates for Simple Workflow>
We are experiencing elevated API failures for AWS Simple Workflow in the EU-WEST-2 Region and continue to work towards full recovery.

<http://status.aws.amazon.com/|Service is operating normally: [RESOLVED] Increased API Error Rates>
Between 8:25 PM and 10:15 PM PDT, we experienced increased API error rates and latencies in the EU-WEST-2 Region. The issue has been resolved and the service is operating normally.

<http://status.aws.amazon.com/|Informational message: [RESOLVED] Elevated error rates for Simple Workflow>
We are experiencing elevated API failures for AWS Simple Workflow in the EU-WEST-2 Region and continue to work towards full recovery.

<http://status.aws.amazon.com/|Service is operating normally: [RESOLVED] Elevated error rates for Simple Workflow>
Between 9:15 PM and 10:30 PM PDT we experienced elevated API failures for AWS Simple Workflow in the EU-WEST-2 Region. The issue has been resolved and the service is operating normally.
